  m_text: "This is the simplest water shader of the group.  Because it\u2019s meant
    to be applied to larger bodies of water, it has two different sets of scrolling
    normals for the surface ripples - one large, one small - to break up the repetition
    of the ripples. It also fades the ripples out at a distance both to hide the
    tiling patterns and to give the lake a mirror finish at a distance."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
